From 9ba208d0f4e590463af4b43c4f5c4449a35b4666 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: DisplayXR Dev <dev@displayxr.local>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 16:32:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] inline-3d(#625): mac DP-composited 2D-overlay atlas on the
 composited-surface weave

The mac composited-surface weave now composites the browser#18-excluded 2D
overlays through the runtime DP overlay-atlas (Windows-parity: final =
woven*(1-a)+overlay), instead of the browser reading renderer-owned overlay
backings on the GPU thread (which lost the mac Graphite single-writer-XOR-reader
race during scroll -> dropped overlay -> flicker). WeaveCompositedSurface builds
a persistent window-sized premul atlas (no per-frame clear; redraw only readable
overlays, keep last-good on a mid-write read, erase vacated rects) and stages it
via SetBatchOverlayMac; gpu_mac MTL-blits it into a kIOSurfaceIsGlobal surface so
the runtime service can IOSurfaceLookup it cross-process. The draw-back reads the
DP-composited overlays from the woven scratch, never the renderer backings.
Result: tiles solid, header + plates crisp with transparency, no present-time
read race. (Residual hover-plate scroll flicker was page-side; fixed in the
gallery.)
